{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre"]]},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"Using URL Templates when defining tile sources","type":"text"}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/Customizing_Fonts","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/Info.plist_Keys","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/GestureRecognizers","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/MultipleImagesExample","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/Predicates_and_Expressions","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/For_Style_Authors"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Other-Articles","title":"Other Articles"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNTileSource"},{"type":"text","text":" objects, specifically "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNRasterTileSource"},{"type":"text","text":" and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNVectorTileSource"},{"type":"text","text":" objects, can be created using an initializer that accepts"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"an array of tile URL templates. Tile URL templates are strings that specify the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"URLs of the vector tiles or raster tile images to load. A template resembles an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"absolute URL, but with any number of placeholder strings that the source"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"evaluates based on the tile it needs to load. For example:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"http:\/\/www.example.com\/tiles\/{z}\/{x}\/{y}.pbf","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" could be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"evaluated as ","type":"text"},{"code":"http:\/\/www.example.com\/tiles\/14\/6\/9.pbf","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"http:\/\/www.example.com\/tiles\/{z}\/{x}\/{y}{ratio}.png"},{"text":" could be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"evaluated as ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"http:\/\/www.example.com\/tiles\/14\/6\/9@2x.png"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Tile URL templates are also used to define tilesets in TileJSON manifests or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/maplibre.org\/maplibre-style-spec\/sources\/#raster","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/maplibre.org\/maplibre-style-spec\/sources\/#vector-tiles","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"sources in style JSON files. See the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/mapbox\/tilejson-spec\/tree\/master\/2.2.0","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for information about tile URL templates in the context of a TileJSON or style"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"JSON file."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Tile sources support the following placeholder strings in tile URL templates,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"all of which are optional:"}]},{"type":"table","header":"row","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Placeholder string","type":"text"}]}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Description"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"{x}"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The index of the tile along the map’s x axis according to Spherical Mercator projection. If the value is 0, the tile’s left edge corresponds to the 180th meridian west. If the value is 2^z−1, the tile’s right edge corresponds to the 180th meridian east."}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"{y}","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The index of the tile along the map’s y axis according to Spherical Mercator projection. If the value is 0, the tile’s tile edge corresponds to arctan(sinh(π)), or approximately 85.0511 degrees north. If the value is 2^z−1, the tile’s bottom edge corresponds to −arctan(sinh(π)), or approximately 85.0511 degrees south. The y axis is inverted if the options parameter contains "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNTileSourceOptionTileCoordinateSystem","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" with a value of "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNTileCoordinateSystem\/MLNTileCoordinateSystemTMS","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"{z}"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The tile’s zoom level. At zoom level 0, each tile covers the entire world map; at zoom level 1, it covers ¼ of the world; at zoom level 2, 1⁄16 of the world, and so on. For tiles loaded by a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNRasterTileSource","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" object, whether the tile zoom level matches the map’s current zoom level depends on the value of the source’s tile size as specified in the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNTileSourceOptionTileSize","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" key of the options parameter."}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"{bbox-epsg-3857}","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The tile’s bounding box, expressed as a comma-separated list of the tile’s western, southern, eastern, and northern extents according to Spherical Mercator (EPSG:3857) projection. The bounding box is typically used with map services conforming to the "},{"type":"text","text":"Web Map Service"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol."}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"{quadkey}"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A quadkey indicating both the tile’s location and its zoom level. The quadkey is typically used with ","type":"text"},{"text":"Bing Maps","type":"text"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"{ratio}"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A suffix indicating the resolution of the tile image. The suffix is the empty string for standard resolution displays and "},{"code":"@2x","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" for Retina displays, including displays for which "},{"code":"UIScreen.scale","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is 3."}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"{prefix}","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Two hexadecimal digits chosen such that each visible tile has a different prefix. The prefix is typically used for domain sharding.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]]]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For more information about the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"{x}"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"{y}"},{"text":", and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"{z}"},{"text":" placeholder strings,","type":"text"},{"